Seafoam Islands

Access to:
Either exit: Route 20

Utility:
Surf is required to access and navigate the Seafoam Islands. In Yellow, wild Pokémon can be encountered on B3F and B4F with Surf.
Strength is required to navigate the Seafoam Islands, and to reach Articuno.

Access to:
Either exit: Route 20

Utility:
Surf is required to access and navigate the Seafoam Islands. In Yellow, wild Pokémon can be encountered on B3F and B4F with Surf.
Strength is required to navigate the Seafoam Islands, and to reach Articuno.

Access to:
Exit: Route 20

Places of interest:
Blaine is located here instead of on Cinnabar Island.

Utility:
Surf is required to access the Seafoam Islands.

Access to:
Either exit: Route 20

Utility:
Surf is required to access and navigate the Seafoam Islands. Wild Pokémon can also be encountered on B3F and B4F with Surf.

Access to:
Exit: Route 20

Places of interest:
Blaine's Gym is located here instead of on Cinnabar Island.

Utility:
Surf is required to access and navigate the Seafoam Islands. Wild Pokémon can also be encountered on B4F with Surf.
Strength is required to navigate the Seafoam Islands.

Access to:
Either exit: Route 20

Places of interest:
The Master Trainer for Articuno is located here. He cannot be battled, but will confer the title of Master Trainer on the player for Articuno if the player shows him a Articuno with at least 7500 CP.

Utility:
Sea Skim is required to access and navigate the Seafoam Islands. Wild Pokémon can also be encountered on B3F and B4F with Sea Skim.
Strong Push is required to navigate the Seafoam Islands.
